Here are some of the functions that can be used on strings in Python:
capitalize(): This function capitalizes the first character of a string.
count(): This function counts the number of times a substring appears in a string.
find(): This function returns the index of the first occurrence of a substring in a string.
index(): This function returns the index of the first occurrence of a substring in a string, or raises an exception if the substring is not found.
join(): This function joins a sequence of strings into a single string, using a specified separator.
lower(): This function converts a string to lowercase.
replace(): This function replaces all occurrences of a substring in a string with another string.
split(): This function splits a string into a list of strings, using a specified separator.
strip(): This function removes leading and trailing whitespace from a string.
upper(): This function converts a string to uppercase.

my_string = "Hello, world!"
my_string.capitalize()
'Hello, world!'
my_string.count("l")
3
my_string.find("world")
7
my_string.index("world")
7
my_string.join(["Hello", ",", "world!"])
'Hello, world!'
my_string.lower()
'hello, world!'
my_string.replace("world", "everyone")
'Hello, everyone!'
my_string.split(" ")
['Hello,', 'world!']
my_string.strip()
'Hello, world!'
my_string.upper()
'HELLO, WORLD!'

# Print each character in the string "hello world"
for char in "hello world":
  print(char)

# Print the index and the value of each character in the string "hello world"
for i, char in enumerate("hello world"):
  print(i, char)

# Create a list of the characters in the string "hello world"
chars = [char for char in "hello world"]

# Get the substring "hello" from the string "hello world"
substring = "hello world"[0:5]

# Get the substring "world" from the string "hello world"
substring = "hello world"[5:]

# Get the substring "hello" from the string "hello world"
substring = "hello world"[:5]


#ASCII to string
ascii_code = 65
character = chr(ascii_code)
print(character)

#String to ASCII
character = "A"
ascii_value = ord(character)
print(ascii_value)
